      "summary": "Brodsky & Smith law firm has announced investigations into multiple merger transactions, including Apogee Therapeutics (acquired by AbbVie for $135.11/share), Roku (acquired by Fox for $160/share), TruBridge (acquired by Inventurus for $26.25/share), and Organon (acquired by Sun Pharmaceutical for $14/share). The investigations focus on whether the respective boards breached fiduciary duties by failing to conduct fair processes and whether deal consideration provides fair value to shareholders.",
